metadata.name: Crosswalk Monsoon #252
metadata.description:
The story behind this collection is that there isn't really a story behind this collection. It is the result of play, tinkering, and curiosity.

One of the beautiful things about generative art is how we can achieve drastically different results simply by modifying a few parameters or lines of code. As my first release here on fxhash was 'Sabler', it felt fitting that my release for #fxhashturnsone would itself be a modified version of that 'Sabler' algorithm, albeit giving drastically different results.

It is notable for the fact that this is perhaps my most 'chaotic' collection yet, letting go of carefully considered proportions, angles and positioning and here leaving that in the hands of the computer. In a way, this simple act represents several design decisions I never would have imagined myself making a year ago, highlighting my growth as a generative artist over the past year.

It is also a reflection of the inspiration gained from many of the artists and boundary-pushers in the space that each time unlock and encourage creations beyond the immediate comfort zone. For that, this is a 'Thank You' to all of you.

With that, here's to many more years of generative beauty and inspiration on fxhash and beyond.

As with previous collections, I highly recommend viewing the images at full size and savouring the details and the chaos up close. Pressing 'S' will save a 6000 x 6000 px PNG file.

50% of primary sales will be donated to the Processing Foundation.

metadata.name: Punktwelt #536
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ’s’ to save a png. Press ’4’ to export a high resolution png. Press ’8’ to export a very high resolution png. Press ’e’ to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.description:
Sharing a space that fills us with happiness
    Exploring what is deeply inside 
    Thinking as one and thinking as hive

    A doing so we transcend

    I know you as you know me
    You explore as I explore
    Mirrors of fears to grow
    Mirrors of love to embrace
    Let's keep on as we can
    Discovering the unknown
    That explodes inside each of us
    And is asking to be felt

Released on fx(hash) to celebrate the first birthday of this platform that has transformed our lives and our culture. Thank you mates, developers, artist and collectors. It has been a great year and I hope is the first of many to came.

metadata.name: a pale reflection #141
metadata.description:
a canvas is prepared; grids and vignette applied.

marks are added (or not)

a drawing method is chosen

the drawing method is iterated, resulting in a heavily stippled image

the image is sent to a shader

various maths occur inside the shader

the resulting shaded image is then given a border

and thus to the screen

a pale reflection - original music here: https://rtsixty.bandcamp.com/track/pale-reflection 
listen while waiting to be signed.

99.9% of royalties to original minter.

metadata.name: Wanderer #153
metadata.description:
Wanderer is an algorithm which uses hexagonal Truchet tiles to produce meandering paths of color. Originally created back in February, I am releasing it as part of this week's #fxhashturnsone celebration.

100% of primary sales will go the the Processing foundation.

Thank you to fx(hash) and to the entire generative art community. 

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

For third party license information, please see license.md

metadata.name: Constellations #22
metadata.description:
We look at things that are seemingly random and can't help but form relationships between them. For centuries people of many different nations and cultures have looked up to the skies and perceived patterns, objects, mythical creatures from scattered stars.

This work, initially titled 'Chaos', began as a study for my project 'Gestalt' to explore the idea of working with a foundation of hidden random points and connecting points with curves in interesting ways. Almost by accident I discovered a technique which ended up creating outputs resembling scenes from some otherworldly cosmos. While it produced some visually interesting outputs, they didn't quite fit the direction for 'Gestalt' and only a portion of the algorithm was used. 

The study was recently revisited and further refined to explore something different to 'Gestalt' (yet would nod to it), blur the lines between abstraction and figuration, and lean into the atmospheric moodiness of that once accidental output. 'Constellations' plays with the concept of interconnectivity, the meeting and interacting of hidden elements, and the emergence of patterns and interpretations from chance encounters (or kismet).

---

Released for VerticalCrypto Art invites | LONDON 2022.

---

Controls:
• 'R' reassembles the piece
• 'B' toggles the frame

Note: Some mints may take time to fully render in live mode.

Made in p5js
Created Oct 2022
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: NAKACHOII #263
metadata.description:
*Nakachoii*
The Nakachoii soldiers from anime lands entered fxhash, this time to get new faces and new powers with the coding that is applied to them. Every time they are minted, and every time a new hash is generated, a new power is given to them. The Nakachoii soldier will fit inside your wallet and protect it with these powers. We are very happy that we gained so much experience on fxhash during its first year, and finally, we were able to create a great project based on all these experiences. Nakachoii is ready to create beauty.
